
sample_kdc: Show how to use KDC to derive a key from given base key id

The container should be run in MISSION lifecycle. Keysplit can be
programmed by running the sample_otp_slot container otherwise empty
keysplit gets used for key derivation.

Note that the field `use_otp_keys` in footer.json must have permit to use the
key split in question.

To load container:
$ mwtest.py -c100 run sample_kdc.img

Sending DGOK as base key id to the container triggers the KDC derive:
$ printf '\000\000\000\000' > testfile
$ cmtest data -f100 testfile

Sending key split 3 as base key id to the container triggers the KDC derive:
$ printf '\024\000\000\000' > testfile
$ cmtest data -f100 testfile

To unload container:
$ mwtest.py -c100 unload
